    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "postgresql"
      },
      "description": "Per-validator APY for the selected subnet. Formula: `dividend \u00d7 (alpha_out_emission / alpha_stake) \u00d7 (1 \u2212 owner_cut) \u00d7 0.5 \u00d7 BLOCKS_PER_YEAR \u00d7 100`, where BLOCKS_PER_YEAR = 2,629,800 (31,557,600 s/yr \u00f7 12 s/block) and the 0.5 is the validator/miner split (chain constant). Denominator is `alpha_stake`, so this is the alpha-denominated yield \u2014 what a unit of alpha exposure earns. Inputs: `mm.dividend` (validator share of subnet dividends, normalised 0..1), `s.alpha_out_emission` (per-block alpha emission; effectively 1 TAO/block \u2014 falls back to 1e9 rao when DB column is 0), `s.owner_cut` (subnet owner cut; falls back to 0.09 when not synced from chain), `ns.alpha_stake` (alpha stake in rao). Windows (1h / 1d / 1w / 1m) anchor to MAX(block.timestamp) for this subnet's validator snapshots \u2014 Grafana's time picker is ignored. Caveats: `validator_take` (per-hotkey commission) not included so APY is gross; `owner_cut` is constant across subnets; multi-mechanism subnets only use mech_id = 0.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "custom": {
            "align": "auto",
            "cellOptions": {
              "type": "auto"
            },
            "inspect": false
